==English==
===Etymology===
From Ancient Egyptian for "papyrus colored", an allusion to the skin of the [[cobra]].

===Proper noun===
'''Wadjet'''

#{{Mythology}} the patron goddess and namesake of the Ancient Egyptian city of [[Per-Wadjit]], known as Buto to the Greeks. Wadjet takes the form of a cobra and is associated with the Eye of [[Horus]].

